[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating class loading mechanisms**\n\nI'm considering how to handle class loading with Constructors. It seems if fresh class static fields are null, there could be issues if other code is loaded. I need to create logs using both variants of Class.forName. The first variant checks the current class loader, and if it cannot find the class, it falls back to the second variant. I wonder about managing visibility between class loaders for proper logging without conflicts. A custom ClassLoader might be necessary to control access.\n\n**Checking class loading diagnostics**\n\nI'm thinking through how `getLowest` checks if TCCL is a child of the current class loader; if it is, it returns TCCL. If the blocking loader fails, I see that using `Class.forName(name)` via LogFactoryImpl succeeds, which is good! Next, I need to ensure that `getResource` and `getSystemResource` only run if diagnostics are enabled. I should check the diagnostics property in Commons Logging and maybe inspect the constants using `javap -v` or `strings`.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0117cd8f1f716fb20169f935a42f08819d826bf94543e6d0a6\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-TWrRqhAXse8oNQb0-KeMQtF76Rixemrd-RtYX39MN4vDW4Laa6EiepnZAI_hwxYXdTUto6WyxHilOJKkmQmMCNBBfg6TZ9ZXWtPlnvbkc2vDQ0_L1l80Y3xT6g-ZiPs3NrmvH0w_e7W-pbphmk_0KVUwmZ9oG0_si71PA92lZkuOcTLVOdzDHjSJLoHg33KzdNWTpJbTZ3geD6osxPTtFVdLepN11A8zE3qlj0d19SZf1w0ckr1Ew8dLwMx2Of5Sa8lZvAjUhkC23cXGvfTWBfqq-QeArti5iagqo8petUP40zzhIU0deMtEHpEJWZvEwa3J8KMrL4pPPfwC5KvfvZXFWdca-4OdIBw1sBl70_ZC_Wi9snKErsYMK5ppBzjS9xWA1O0-nlVi1YfEPt7yf_l6TBxAVV-Hz7MvMQrMCn6aJNM0XDDIcatw7ySVtLaCVKkx3R6fxLreOndVqEErGm2turq5-j0i2-H178I_PChHN4HyEM2XiW_E1u-TF0wDMVUjvoh74BOk6wPPRNB7SLxjzLx5r7WwWE_pJTwH0YEcD4bw6FaBdlDgFvIXj6hSIFdCXMIYt-P_sswPYVmJ03V9cK82zV4xCWORbCp7MsZIZyVzVIrz-HZ9E6cB8FTAP7ylBtNXUS4xA_TFEPwIK_gKSLaVjl1R4cL-wl6-DCk0SCM_BvliuAbR9iG7dXmSRFWyU